.TH WARDEN\-MCP 1 "2026-06-29" "0.2.28" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
warden\-mcp \- Vaultwarden/Bitwarden MCP server for AI agents
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B warden-mcp
[\fB\-\-stdio\fR | \fB\-\-http\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B warden-mcp
is a Model Context Protocol (MCP) server that lets AI agents interact with
Vaultwarden or Bitwarden password vaults via the official Bitwarden CLI
(\fBbw\fR). MCP clients can search, create, update, move, and read vault
items without reimplementing Bitwarden client-side cryptography.
.PP
By default the server starts in HTTP/SSE mode and listens on port 3005.
Pass \fB\-\-stdio\fR to use stdin/stdout transport for direct embedding in
desktop MCP hosts.
.PP
The Bitwarden CLI (\fBbw\fR) must be available on PATH, or its location
set via the \fBBW_BIN\fR environment variable.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-stdio
Use stdio transport. The MCP host communicates over stdin/stdout.
.TP
.B \-\-http
Use HTTP/SSE transport (default). Listens on the port defined by \fBPORT\fR.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B BW_HOST
URL of the Vaultwarden or Bitwarden server.
.TP
.B BW_CLIENTID
Bitwarden API client ID for API-key authentication.
.TP
.B BW_CLIENTSECRET
Bitwarden API client secret for API-key authentication.
.TP
.B BW_USER
Bitwarden account email for username/password authentication.
.TP
.B BW_PASSWORD
Bitwarden master password.
.TP
.B BW_BIN
Path to the \fBbw\fR CLI binary. Overrides automatic detection.
.TP
.B PORT
TCP port to listen on in HTTP mode (default: \fB3005\fR).
.TP
.B WARDEN_MCP_HOST
IP address or hostname to bind to in HTTP mode.
.TP
.B WARDEN_MCP_STDIO
Set to \fBtrue\fR to enable stdio mode without passing \fB\-\-stdio\fR.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Start in HTTP mode with API-key authentication:
.RS
.nf
BW_HOST=https://vault.example.com \\
BW_CLIENTID=user.xxxxx \\
BW_CLIENTSECRET=xxxxx \\
BW_PASSWORD='master-password' \\
warden-mcp
.fi
.RE
.PP
Start in stdio mode for Claude Code:
.RS
.nf
BW_HOST=https://vault.example.com \\
BW_USER=user@example.com \\
BW_PASSWORD='master-password' \\
warden-mcp --stdio
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
